11 (3) A vacancy in the task force must be filled in the same manner as members are appointed
12 under subsection (1).
13 (4) By June 30, 2027, the task force shall report to the governor and the economic affairs interim
14 committee.
15 (5) The task force is allocated to the department of fish, wildlife, and parks for administrative
16 purposes only as provided in 2-15-121.
17 (6) (a) Except as provided in subsection (6)(b) and unless otherwise provided by law, each
18 member is entitled to be paid $100 for each day in which the member is engaged in the performance of duties
19 under this section and is also entitled to be reimbursed for travel expenses, as provided for in 2-18-501 through
20 2-18-503, incurred while performing task force duties.
21 (b) Members who are full-time, salaried officers or employees of this state or of a political
22 subdivision of this state are not entitled to be compensated for their service as members except when they
23 perform their task force duties outside of their regular working hours or during hours charged against their leave
24 time, but those members are entitled to be reimbursed for travel expenses as provided for in 2-18-501 through
25 2-18-503.
